Description: Luchismart is a cutting-edge cloud-based access control company that specializes in providing secure and intelligent solutions for business
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Luchismart is a cutting-edge cloud-based access control company that specializes in providing secure and intelligent solutions for modern businesses and organizations. With the aim of revolutionizing traditional access control systems, Luchismart combines advanced technology and innovative features to deliver a seamless and efficient access management experience. At the core of Luchismart's offerings is its robust cloud infrastructure, which enables organizations to manage access permissions and monitor activities remotely from anywhere in the world. By leveraging the power of the cloud, Luchismart eliminates the need for on-premises servers, simplifying the installation process and reducing maintenance costs. Luchismart offers a wide range of access control solutions tailored to meet the unique needs of various industries, including corporate offices, educational institutions, healthcare facilities, government agencies, and more. Whether it's securing entry points, managing visitor access, or restricting access to sensitive areas, Luchismart's scalable and customizable solutions provide comprehensive control over who can enter and exit premises. One of Luchismart's standout features is its intelligent access management system, which incorporates advanced analytics and machine learning algorithms. By analyzing access patterns and user behavior, Luchismart can detect anomalies and potential security threats in real-time, enabling proactive response and preventing unauthorized access attempts. With a user-friendly interface and intuitive controls, Luchismart ensures a seamless experience for both administrators and end-users. Administrators can easily configure access rules, set up schedules, and generate detailed reports, all from a centralized dashboard. Meanwhile, employees, visitors, or residents can conveniently access authorized areas using various credentials, such as keycards, mobile apps, or biometric authentication. Security is of utmost importance to Luchismart, and the company employs industry-leading encryption protocols and security measures to safeguard sensitive data and ensure privacy. Additionally, Luchismart is designed to integrate with other security systems, such as video surveillance, alarm systems, and intercoms, creating a comprehensive security ecosystem for complete peace of mind. In an era where flexibility, efficiency, and security are paramount, Luchismart stands as a trusted partner for organizations seeking advanced access control solutions. By harnessing the power of the cloud and incorporating intelligent features, Luchismart empowers businesses to enhance security, streamline operations, and embrace the future of access control management.

Description: Rochelle Porter Design is an sustainable lifestyle brand specializing in vibrant textiles derived from the founder's original artwork.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Rochelle Porter has never met a blank surface she didn’t want to draw on. A lifelong lover of global design traditions, the Atlanta-based artist takes cues from the breezy hues of her Guyanese roots, the stark simplicity of Scandinavian design and the boldness of West African weaves to create vibrant, eye-catching textiles for athleisure, accessories and home decor. Her travel-inspired patterns feature joyful, unexpected bursts of color, and classic motifs with a fresh, modern twist. After learning of the unethical labor practices of today’s “fast fashion” industry, Rochelle nearly abandoned her dream of becoming a designer. That is, until she discovered that style could also be sustainable. Combining her passion for patterns with her commitment to responsible manufacturing, she created Rochelle Porter Design (RPD), a lifestyle brand specializing in thoughtfully made goods. True to its tagline, “Design for abundant living,” the company believes everyone along the value chain should have the chance to live well—from the farmer who picks the pesticide-free organic cotton for its textiles, to the customer who puts them on her sofa. RPD prioritizes fair pay and the use of organic materials whenever possible.

Description: A data science and technology incubator for advacing public health
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Information Exchange and Data Transformation (INFORMED) is an incubator for collaborative regulatory science research focused on supporting innovations that enhance the United States Food and Drug Administration's (FDA) mission of promotion and protection of public health. Drawing from the expertise of a diverse group of physicians, data scientists, statisticians, and entrepreneurs-in-residence, INFORMED is expanding organizational and technical infrastructure for big data analytics and examining modern approaches in evidence generation to support regulatory decisions. Special emphasis is placed on systems thinking in regulatory science research to facilitate the development and adoption of new solutions for improving efficiency, reliability, and productivity in a broad range of workflows related to drug development and regulatory decision making. The research portfolio of INFORMED includes investigations into the use of real world data for clinical evidence generation and prospective pragmatic clinical trials, testing the utility of biosensors and the internet of things to quantify intrinsic and extrinsic (e.g., environmental) factors influencing the patient’s experience, identifying opportunities for machine learning and artificial intelligence to improve existing practices, and exploring the utility of open-access platforms and emerging technologies such as blockchain to enable secure exchange of health data at scale. In addition, INFORMED is actively pursuing the development of programs to support creation of a knowledgeable, sustainable, and agile data science workforce capable of addressing the needs of cancer patients in today’s technology-driven and connected world.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Biotechnology, Data and Analytics, Health Care, Information Technology, Science and Engineering, Software

Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: My passion for technology began during childhood. I would disassemble radios and televisions for fun. When I was nine years old, I created a surround sound system for my bedroom by attaching random speakers I had pulled out of broken radio's into a Zenith AM/FM radio. My family still pokes fun about the UHF antennae I made using wood and wire hangers. AV Solutions was created to fulfill my lifelong dream of working with technology and electronics. The "solutions" part of the name incorporates my vision of providing the solution to any "audio and video" want or need that our customers desire. Whether creating total home automation, the home theater of your dreams, or upgrading or troubleshooting existing equipment - AV Solutions is the answer. AV Solutions has grown by word of mouth and referrals with no advertising. A prestigious home theater company in Atlanta frequently refers their customers to us, which has also added to our strong growth.

Description: Virtueconomy is a goodness-mobilizing social enterprise that converts consumer purchases into empowering services for nonprofits
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Virtueconomy is a for-profit social enterprise that converts sales from socially conscious small businesses into uplifting and empowering nonprofit services.  Compared to for-profit businesses, nonprofits face significant double standards when it comes to overhead expenditure. Most donors have a visceral aversion to overheads, wanting a majority of their donation to go directly to the cause and not towards compensation, advertising & marketing spend, investment in IT and innovation etc. Sadly, this 'Overhead Myth' is crippling the nonprofit sector, stagnating innovation and destroying growth potential. ​It seems counterintuitive that the very organizations that have altruistically committed themselves to making the world a better place, are often constrained from maximally doing so! ​We empower nonprofits to break free from the "The Nonprofit Starvation Cycle" by providing services that help them not just to survive, but to grow! Rather than handouts, we provide leg-ups in areas that they need it most.  Here's how it works: 1) Consumers purchase products from our ecommerce partners 2) A set percentage from each sale is paid by these businesses to Virtueconomy 3) ​We then convert those funds into valuable services for the matched nonprofit partner As a male founder, it was important to me to become an ally and stand up for the gender inequality that continues to persist in the business world.  As such, Virtueconomy's initial focus is on Women Empowerment -- We create shared value by matching female founded enterprises with relevant nonprofits that empower, educate and uplift women.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Social Impact, Software
